In this Cedar/East Bethel home, we transformed a sprawling layout including the entryway, kitchen hallway, and living room from a dated "old-school" green and heavy beige to a vibrant, cohesive sanctuary. The renewal features a sophisticated Deep Sea Blue accent that creates a bold focal point, perfectly balanced by a "Different Scented" light-reflective beige on the surrounding walls to keep the halls feeling open and airy. By updating these high-traffic transition spaces, we eliminated the disjointed feel of the previous palette and replaced it with a modern, intentional flow. This project showcases how the right "blue-to-beige" ratio can add personality to a home without sacrificing a sense of clean, professional order.